Product Id: Screened traffic includes both passengers and non-passengers screened at Pre-Board Screening (PBS) checkpoints at Canada's eight largest airports.

The eight largest airports in Canada include: Halifax/Robert L. Stanfield, Montréal/Pierre Elliott Trudeau, Ottawa/Macdonald-Cartier, Toronto/Lester B. Pearson, Winnipeg/James Armstrong Richardson, Calgary International, Edmonton International and Vancouver International.

Non-passenger data are comprised of non-passengers screened at Pre-Board Screening (PBS) checkpoints but does not include non-passengers screened at Non-Passenger Screening (NPS) checkpoints. Some examples of non-passengers screened at PBS checkpoints include flight and cabin crews as well as airport staff who aid passengers through the PBS checkpoints.
